execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:30:- **work-backward-from-constraint.md** — NEW (thermal-time strategy-001 meta-exploration-002): For constructive explorations, frame the task as "what theory/value satisfies this constraint?" rather than forward-computing predictions. Produces definitive answers anchored to constraints and unexpected byproducts (e.g., no-go theorems, uniqueness conditions). Contrast: forward framing generates correct calculations that may not resolve the key question; backward framing forces a definitive derivation. Structure: (1) identify the constraint, (2) derive what satisfies it, (3) check consistency, (4) allow unexpected results.
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:45:- **definition-extraction-gates-computation.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure E001), UPDATED (anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall meta-001, exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit meta-001, exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall meta-001): Before computation phases, run a definition-extraction exploration ("Phase 0") reading primary sources to verify the team's understanding of the target quantity, event, or theorem object. Prevents the most wasteful failure: computing the wrong thing due to incorrect mental model. Vasseur-pressure: team assumed beta = pressure integrability; Phase 0 revealed beta = De Giorgi recurrence exponent. **Updates:** if Phase 0 only needs the mechanism architecture, partial primary-source access can still be sufficient; if architecture is already known locally, one exact law from primary sources can be the missing layer that closes the definition gate; if exact-PDE post-processing plus observability conventions already defines the object, prefer that over inventing a reduced model.
