execution/agents/library/factual/INDEX.md:3:Organized knowledge base covering the major approaches to quantum gravity, cross-cutting themes, systematic constraints, "gravitize the quantum" programs, the Riemann hypothesis, the Yang-Mills existence & mass gap problem, the Navier-Stokes regularity problem, the Compton-Unruh resonance hypothesis, the classicality budget, stochastic electrodynamics (SED), the amplituhedron/scattering amplitudes program (including surfaceology), the Connes-Rovelli Thermal Time Hypothesis, and Barandes' indivisible stochastic dynamics (ISP). 377 findings across 21 top-level categories. (**exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall exploration-003**: the preferred delayed-transfer precursor pair fails structurally — the exact filtered-energy balance has no backward-memory link from the later flux/witness event to the earlier slab, so no identity-only no-hidden-transfer theorem exists; 1 new entry, 2 factual updates. Prior: **exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall exploration-002**: the preferred earlier-warning pair for the exact delayed-transfer event is earlier cumulative positive forward flux on the predecessor slab of the same parabolic cylinder; Duchon-Robert remains backup only, and the event entry is now sharpened toward the quantitative no-hidden-transfer test; 1 new entry, 1 factual update. Prior: **exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall exploration-001**: the faithful exact-NS physical-space continuation survives the earlier Tao-object failures — the preferred event is a localized delayed forward-flux burst with subscale witness gain on a parabolic cylinder; coarse-graining is observability rather than model reduction, and Duchon-Robert is backup only; 1 new entry, 2 factual updates. Prior: **exact-ns-tiny-trigger-firewall exploration-001**: trigger-focused narrowing does not produce a smaller faithful exact-NS object — the only faithful trigger object is the prior five-role helical hypergraph with `a3` distinguished, so the predecessor singleton impossibility transfers immediately and the packetized backup remains non-canonical; 1 new entry, 2 factual updates. Prior: **exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit exploration-001**: the Phase 0 definition gate for Tao's exact-NS firewall passes — the right object is a finite helical support plus a five-role monomial hypergraph and coefficient-weighted leakage ratio, and the spectator-coupling test is now an exact desired-vs-leakage ledger rather than a vague packet-isolation slogan; 1 new entry, 1 factual update. Prior: **anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall exploration-002**: exact Phase 1 firewall for Tao's averaged-NS blowup narrowed to two mechanism-level candidates — triadic coefficient rigidity and unavoidable spectator couplings inside the exact projected triad network; 2 new entries, 1 factual update. Prior: **anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall exploration-001**: Tao averaged NS blowup reconstructed as a delayed-abrupt-transfer five-mode circuit embedded in a shell cascade; the concrete firewall question for exact NS is whether its triads can realize the same independently engineered couplings while keeping trigger variables energetically negligible; 1 new entry, 1 factual update. Earlier: **far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole exploration-001**: exact far-field obstruction reconstruction — harmonic `P_{k1}` is already favorable; the surviving far-field harmonic loophole is a decomposition mismatch, not Vasseur's literal bottleneck `P_{k21}`; any live route must show an alternative near/far split makes the pressure factor `U_k`-dependent; 1 new entry, 2 factual updates. Earlier: **vasseur-pressure S2-E008**: Chebyshev bound PROVABLY TIGHT for div-free fields — constant field u=(c,0,0) achieves ratio->1; all 4 De Giorgi chain steps individually tight under NS constraints; beta = 4/3 SHARP (rigorous) within De Giorgi-Vasseur framework; SDP formalization unnecessary — analytic extremizer is elementary; div-free level-set question RESOLVED; 1 new entry, 4 updates. Earlier: S2-E007 adversarial review, S2-E006 non-CZ pressure, S2-E005 LP obstruction, S2-E002 DNS level-set distribution, S2-E004 compensated compactness, S2-E003 Chebyshev universality, S2-E001 sharpness audit, E010 near-Beltrami definitive negative, E009 adversarial, E007 Beltrami deficit, E008 vorticity/H^1, E005 CV14, E006 Beltrami, E004 CZ slack.)
