plies regularity; current beta < 4/3 from `P_k^{21}` bottleneck; DNS measurement approaches TESTED; DNS results: all beta_eff < 4/3 (max 1.01 ABC); bottleneck gamma DECREASES with Re (gap genuine); ABC Beltrami uniquely favorable; CZ slack for `P_k^{21}` k-INDEPENDENT — FALSIFIES improvement hypothesis; `P21` has LESS CZ slack than full pressure; Tran-Yu Galilean invariance ORTHOGONAL; pressure Poisson equation Galilean-invariant; Choi-Vasseur 2014 three-way decomposition (beta=7/6, does NOT bypass bottleneck); post-2007: NO paper has improved beta beyond 4/3; Fernandez-Dalgo 2025 dynamic pressure (epsilon-regularity, not De Giorgi); **Vasseur-Yang 2021 vorticity De Giorgi: pressure eliminated but UNIVERSAL 4/3 barrier from trilinear form (1/2 + 5/6 = 4/3, quadratic nonlinearity, NOT pressure-specific); H^1 pressure route structurally dead (W^{1,3} wall); exact far-field obstruction reconstruction: harmonic `P_{k1}` is already favorable, so the surviving far-field harmonic loophole is a decomposition mismatch, not literal `P_{k21}`.**); **geometric regularity criteria** (Constantin-Fefferman, Beirao da Veiga-Berselli Holder-1/2 — Beltrami connection); **Beltrami pressure analytical** (p=-|u|^2/2, zero CZ loss, trivially regular); **near-Beltrami perturbation** (bad pressure O(eps), continuous degradation, truncation obstacle RESOLVED by E007); **E009 ADVERSARIAL: DNS tightness limited by smooth-solution regime; Beltrami-De Giorgi connection strongest finding; truncation preservation WEAKEST CLAIM. E010 DEFINITIVE NEGATIVE: Beltrami-De Giorgi mechanism does NOT generalize — B_k decay, Bernoulli dominance, and beta>1 all specific to exact Beltrami; mechanism is measure-zero; Leray projection minor. S2-E001: Proposition 3 sharpness audit — sensitivity table, 5/6 genealogy, 5 free parameters exhausted, Chebyshev on NS is single improvable step. S2-E004: compensated compactness / commutator route DEFINITIVELY CLOSED — three-layer obstruction (no div-curl, commutator remainder 61% of P^{21}, CRW vacuous); SQG-NS structural gap (scalar/vector, linear/quadratic); beta = 4/3 sharp within energy+Sobolev+CZ+Chebyshev class. S2-E002: DNS level-set distribution tails IC-dependent (TG p~10, Random p~8-9, ABC p~2.1 < 10/3); Chebyshev tightness ratios ~3-5x and k-independent (constant slack, NOT beta-improving). S2-E005: frequency-localized De Giorgi via LP CLOSED — Bernstein exchange rate 2^{3j/5} dimensional, CZ is optimal frequency-by-frequency estimate, LP 5-10x worse; paraproduct transition (resonance low k, paraproduct high k); direction 2 closed. S2-E006: non-CZ pressure routes (IBP beta=1, H^1/BMO beta=4/3, CRW beta<=1) — beta=4/3 TOOL-INDEPENDENT (locked to NS quadratic structure, not analytical method); CZ consolidation gain exactly 1/3; 12 published approaches surveyed, none beat 4/3; Wolf local decomposition and Tran-Yu depletion genuinely untested; 3 remaining directions. S2-E007: ADVERSARIAL REVIEW CONFIRMS OBSTRUCTION — all 7 closures survive attack, 3 combination attacks fail, 15-paper lit search + Vasseur 2025 survey (arXiv:2503.02575) confirms no improvement, Tao 2016 supercritical connection sharpened to an engineered five-mode circuit question; novel claim rankings (Claim 3 seven-route obstruction most significant at 8/10); Claims 1-4 combined publishable; SDP formalization top priority. S2-E008: Chebyshev bound PROVABLY TIGHT for div-free fields — constant field u=(c,0,0) achieves ratio->1; all 4 De Giorgi chain steps individually tight; beta = 4/3 SHARP (rigorous); div-free level-set question RESOLVED; SDP unnecessary**; 56 findings (27 + 29 in vasseur-de-giorgi/ subfolder)
