execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:31:- **include-trivial-control-checks.md** — NEW (thermal-time meta-003), UPDATED (vasseur-pressure E007): Every computation exploration should include one "should equal X by construction" check (different code path, limit case, or symmetry). The thermal-time E003 control check C_global = C_full (at machine zero for all λ) confirmed that the 82.7% discrepancy was physical, not a bug. Cost: near zero. Payoff: immediate trust or bug detection. **NEW variants (E007):** known-answer validation at exact-solution conditions (t=0 Beltrami sanity check caught sign error propagated from prior code), and verify mathematical identity before building measurements (div(u_below) != 0 invalidated prescribed Lamb decomposition).
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:32:- **structural-vs-quantitative-discrepancy.md** — NEW (thermal-time meta-003): When two predictions disagree, diagnose whether the discrepancy is structural (different signal topology — wrong number of peaks, different symmetry class) or quantitative (scale factor, coefficient). Parameter tuning cannot fix structural discrepancies — they require a different model. In E003, C_full had two FFT peaks and C_local had one — no value of ω_eff can make a single sinusoid match a beating signal. Ask in goals: "Is the discrepancy structural or quantitative?"
