## Entries

- **tao-averaged-ns-delayed-transfer-circuit.md** — Tao's averaged-NS blowup mechanism is a deliberately engineered five-mode delayed-abrupt-transfer circuit embedded in a shell cascade, not a vague "dyadic cascade" slogan. Averaging preserves energy cancellation/scaling but not the exact local NS tensor structure. Key reduced roles: `X1,n` carrier, `X2,n` clock, `X3,n` tiny trigger, `X4,n` conduit, `X1,n+1` next carrier. The sharpened exact-NS firewall question is whether real triads can realize the same independently tuned couplings/signs while suppressing parasitic interactions; later precursor work fixes the best physical-space handoff as forward flux plus subscale witness gain. [VERIFIED]
- **exact-helical-near-closed-tao-circuit-definition.md** — Phase 0 definition gate PASSES: a near-closed Tao circuit can be stated exactly on a finite sign-closed helical support with a five-role target hypergraph and a coefficient-weighted leakage ratio. Exact data and user tolerances are now explicitly separated. Singleton amplitude-level bookkeeping is the preferred Phase 1 object; packet-energy models are backup only. [CHECKED]
- **exact-trigger-object-not-standalone.md** — A Tao-style tiny trigger is not a standalone theorem object in exact NS. Making "tiny before threshold, decisive after threshold" precise forces the full carrier/clock/conduit/output chain back in, so the faithful trigger object is just the prior five-role helical model with `a3` distinguished. The predecessor singleton negative and packet non-canonicity therefore transfer immediately. [CHECKED]
- **exact-singleton-tao-circuit-nonembeddability.md** — The preferred singleton-support exact Tao-circuit object is structurally impossible. The desired `a1^2 -> a2` and `a1^2 -> a3` channels force roles 2 and 3 onto the same conjugate wavevector pair, after which the amplifier `a2 a3 -> a3` cannot satisfy exact triad closure for any sign choice. Stronger than a leakage obstruction: the sharp exact object dies before coefficient analysis. [COMPUTED]
- **packetized-tao-circuit-noncanonical.md** — The packetized backup does not rescue the theorem program. Once packetization is introduced, the object depends on packet support, projection, leakage scalarization, and network-restoration conventions, so it is no longer one canonical exact-NS object. Packet canonization would still be a separate mission; later continuation instead bypassed packets entirely via the exact-NS physical-space flux/witness event. [CHECKED]
- **exact-ns-physical-space-delayed-transfer-event.md** — The faithful physical-space exact-NS analogue of Tao's delayed handoff is a localized burst of positive forward interscale flux across one coarse-graining scale together with abrupt gain in a subscale band-energy witness after an earlier quiet interval. Filtering is observability, not reduced dynamics; Duchon-Robert is backup only; the clean no-hidden-transfer continuation on the selected same-family precursor is later closed negatively. [CHECKED]
- **exact-ns-delayed-transfer-precursor-pair.md** — The preferred earlier-warning pair for the exact delayed-transfer event is cumulative positive `Pi_ell` mass on the disjoint predecessor slab of the same parabolic cylinder. It survives the tautology screen because it drops the later witness clause and stays on a fixed earlier interval; Duchon-Robert is backup only; later work shows the pair still lacks the exact backward-memory needed for an identity-only no-hidden-transfer theorem. [CHECKED]
- **exact-ns-delayed-transfer-precursor-no-backward-memory.md** — The preferred delayed-transfer precursor pair fails structurally at the theorem stage: subtracting the filtered balances at `ell/rho` and `ell` controls only the final-window witness gain, boundary transport, and viscous band terms, while the earlier slab `R_-` never appears. So no theorem `P_flux^-(R_-) <= epsilon => E_flux impossible` follows from exact identities alone. [CHECKED]
- **exact-ns-triadic-coefficient-rigidity.md** — Exact NS gives one Fourier-triad interaction law with geometry- and projector-fixed coefficients, not Tao's five independently engineered gate strengths. The live question is whether any exact support can realize Tao's full sign/size hierarchy inside that rigidity. [CHECKED]
- **exact-ns-unavoidable-spectator-couplings.md** — Exact NS activates the full projected triad network plus mirror-mode bookkeeping, so Tao's desired channels do not come alone. After the definition gate, the stress test is exact: write the desired / internal-leakage / external-leakage ledger on a minimal helical support and see whether any adversarially favorable helicity choice can keep leakage genuinely subordinate. [CHECKED]

### Vortex Stretching Slack (E003, adversarial E008)
- **adversarial-minimum-vs-slack.md** — Anti-parallel vortex tubes at sigma=2.5 achieve converged minimum VS slack of 157.70x (N=128), 34% below Taylor-Green vortex's 236.90x. Bowl-shaped sigma-dependence. Five-IC comparison. Near-Re-independent (157-175x across Re=100-1000). **E008: Protas-type PDE-optimized ICs (JFM 2020) not tested — strongest untested challenge.** [COMPUTED, CHECKED]
- **vortex-stretching-structural-slack.md** — The 158x minimum slack is a **lower bound over tested ICs** (NOT irreducible). Two sources: Holder step (S-omega misalignment) and Ladyzhenskaya step (extremizer mismatch). 3-factor decomposition (63% Lad, 31% geom, 6% sym) is **tautological by construction** but correctly identifies Ladyzhenskaya as dominant bottleneck. **E008: Protas ICs untested; domain-size dependent; decomposition TGV-specific.** [CHECKED, CONJECTURED]
- **beltrami-zero-vortex-stretching.md** — ABC flow (Beltrami: omega=u) has VS=0 identically at all times by incompressibility. Z-invariant vortex tubes also have VS=0 due to strain-vorticity orthogonality. Breaking z-symmetry (sinusoidal modulation) restores nonzero VS. [COMPUTED]

### Spectral Ladyzhenskaya Analysis (E006, adversarial E008)
- **spectral-ladyzhenskaya-negative-result.md** — Spectral support alone CANNOT improve sharp Ladyzhenskaya constant as worst-case bound. LP cross terms dominate (63% for Kolmogorov). Phase-optimized fields achieve near-sharp constants. **E008: phase optimization may be stuck in local optima (L-BFGS-B on non-convex landscape); Bernstein inequality offers alternative interpolation path.** Verdict: INCONCLUSIVE (directionally correct, not rigorous). [COMPUTED, CHECKED]
- **gaussian-effective-ladyzhenskaya.md** — In the Gaussian random-phase regime (CLT), C_{L,eff} = 3^{1/4}(||f||/||∇f||)^{3/4}. For Kolmogorov spectra: C_{L,eff} ≈ 1.707 × Re^{-3/8}. TYPICAL-case only, not a bound. [COMPUTED, CHECKED]

